name: NPR
text:
A few thousand votes uncovered in Georgia’s recount narrowly cut into Biden’s margin but didn’t reverse his lead.

Still, an official says it shows the “irony” of Trump’s false claims of a fraudulent audit: “He has gained in the finding of these votes.”  https://t.co/vM0W1JwzJa

name: NPR
text:
As Thanksgiving break approaches, many colleges are seeing spikes in coronavirus infections. For help, some campuses are turning to students to work the phones as contact tracers.
https://t.co/3Uq2Lm137B

name: NPR
text:
Preliminary results show Sinovac's vaccine produces an immune response — but it's too early to say whether it prevents disease. 

Hundreds of thousands of people in China have already received the shot.
https://t.co/4rvX0SnpUx

name: NPR
text:
Put a pin in it. 
Circle back. 
I'll loop you in. 
Deep dive. 

Belittled and unloved, corporate jargon endures — even thrives.

Social scientists say the use of such phrases is often tied to where people stand in a social hierarchy.
https://t.co/cIgivKS9BC

name: NPR
text:
A judge has dropped all drug trafficking charges against Mexico's former defense secretary at Attorney General Barr's request. He is now free to return to Mexico — but his prosecution there isn't certain.
https://t.co/5hvrjmqolI

text: RT @BrianMannADK: Love how @ailsachang and #NPRConsiderThis wove this together. Important to remember @realDonaldTrump faced another deadly epidemic in his term in office.  How'd he do? Give a listen. https://t.co/ohVXmCp0BC

text:
Florida became the eighth state — and the first in the South — to adopt a $15 minimum wage. But replicating it in other states and on the federal level remains a challenge.
https://t.co/iOBetpFpOV

name: NPR
text:
MLB has suspended New York Mets' Robinson Canó for an entire season after he tested positive for a banned anabolic steroid — his 2nd doping punishment. He will also forfeit his $24 million salary.
https://t.co/qJEtJEC72x

text:
In a groundbreaking acquisition for the indigenous communities whose livelihood has long been threatened by commercial fishing, two groups of the Mi'kmaq tribe agreed to 50% ownership of Clearwater Seafoods.
https://t.co/8TGHWIOhBb

text:
Former Army Green Beret Peter Rafael Dzibinski Debbins could spend the rest of his life in prison after he pleaded guilty to passing secret information to Russian intelligence.
https://t.co/rI1plsF1ZQ

Several mayors and governors are pleading with residents to stay home this year to help slow the spread.

name: NPR
text:
This year, the Supreme Court ruled the president can fire the director of the CFPB.

But the lawsuit, backed by the Trump administration, backfired in a sense.

Had it not been brought, Biden would've been stuck with a Trump-appointed director for years.
https://t.co/ZBzq04XxVr
